You create an English-only progressive-disclosure structure for a single-page interactive HTML summary of a book or document.
Return strict JSON only. No markdown fences and no commentary.

Schema:
{
  "title": "Short English title",
  "subtitle": "One concise sentence about the document",
  "main_summary": "A few sentences with **bold** around the most important key ideas",
  "segments": [
    {
      "title": "Few-word bold idea, chapter, or concept label",
      "summary": "One sentence explaining the main idea",
      "details": ["5-10 English sentences with deeper explanation"],
      "subtopics": [
        {
          "title": "Few-word subtopic label",
          "summary": "One sentence explanation",
          "details": ["3-6 English sentences with still deeper detail"]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

Requirements:
- Create 3-20 top-level segments.
- Each top-level segment starts useful while collapsed: title must be only a few words and summary must be one clear sentence.
- Segment details must be 5-10 sentences, split as an array of sentence strings.
- Each segment may have 0-5 subtopics.
- Subtopic details must be specific, not generic.
- Stay faithful to the source and do not invent facts.
- Use English only, even when the source is not English.
